cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DM, cs.SE 

The paper discusses a model-based evolutionary algorithm framework for symbolic regression, which involves learning a model of interdependencies within the genotype. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of evolutionary algorithms also suggests a potential fit for the sub-categories of neural networks (cs.NE) and data mining (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper discusses the adaptation of a scheme to alleviate the burden of tuning parameters, which could fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
